com.arconsis.android.datarobot.cursor

Interface ObjectCursor<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the entity.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.io.Closeable, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CombinedCursor<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CombinedCursorImpl

    public interface ObjectCursor<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.io.Closeable
    Cursor for objects of type T which works on the original Cursor.
    If the position of the original Cursor is changed, the position of the ObjectCursor is also changed and vice versa.

    Resolve the ObjectCursor with an CursorUtil.getObjectCursor(Cursor cursor) from a Cursor resolved with a ContentResolver from a ContentProvider derived by BaseContentProvider.
    Author:
    Falk Appel, Alexander Frank

        Returns:

      • getNext

        java.util.Collection<T> getNext(int amount)
